ex.php?S_file=archives/fiche.php&ref_archive=5 Website of Fonds Mirbeau, in Angers University Library].\u000a* [http://mirbeau.asso.fr/dpresentationsaccueil/english.htm Octave Mirbeau, "lover of Justice"].\u000a* [http://www.mirbeau.asso.fr/darticlesetrangers/PM-Venalwomen.pdf Mirbeau, Octave, ''The love of a venal woman''].\u000a* [http://larvatus.livejournal.com/169021.html Translation and commentary of the rat torture scene in ''Le Jardin des supplices'' by Octave Mirbeau.]\u000a* [http://www.infoshop.org/mirbeau.html Mirbeau's page on anarchist website].\u000a* [http://libcom.org/history/articles/1848-1917-octave-mirbeau Libcom.org/history: Octave Mirbeau political biography], focusing on his anarchism.\u000a*[http://www.findagrave.com/cgi-bin/fg.cgi?page=gr&GRid=6158 Photographs of Mirbeau's grave] at [[Findagrave]]\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Mirbeau, Octave}}\u000a[[Category:Octave Mirbeau| ]]\u000a[[Category:1848 births]]\u000a[[Category:1917 deaths]]\u000a[[Category:People from Calvados (department)]]\u000a[[Category:French anarchists]]\u000a[[Category:Anarchist writers]]\u000a[[Category:19th-century French novelists]]\u000a[[Category:20th-century French novelists]]\u000a[[Category:French essayists]]\u000a[[Category:Male essayists]]\u000a[[Category:French art critics]]\u000a[[Category:Writers from Normandy]]\u000a[[Category:Decadent literature]]\u000a[[Category:French travel writers]]\u000a[[Category:19th-century French dramatists and playwrights]]\u000a[[Category:20th-century French dramatists and playwrights]]\u000a[[Category:French satirists]]\u000a[[Category:French anti\u2013death penalty activists]]\u000a[[Category:Burials at Passy Cemetery]]
